<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<cfsSimulation xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.cfs++.org/simulation ../../../../../share/xml/CFS-Simulation/CFS.xsd"
  xmlns="http://www.cfs++.org/simulation">

  <documentation>
    <title> rectangular domain with point source in the center and ABC of 1st order</title>
    <authors>
      <author>Paul Maurerlehner</author>
    </authors>
    <date>2024-12-27</date>
    <keywords>
      <keyword>acoustic</keyword>
      <keyword>abc</keyword>
      <keyword>tdef</keyword>
      <keyword>complex material parameters</keyword>
    </keywords>
    <references> PhD thesis Maurerlehner 2023 TU Graz, TDEF paper in Acta Acustica Maurerlehner et
      al. 2025 </references>
    <isVerified>yes</isVerified>
    <description> 2D model of a semi-infinite duct for 1D plane-wave propagation in a strongly
      damped material. The duct is shorter than the wavelength which requires an accurate ABC (NRBC)
      to avoid reflections. The hamonic excitation is simulated in transient analysis based on the
      TDEF formulation and the in a harmonic analysis based on the complex fluid formulation. The
      analytic solution of the problem can be computed as p(omega,t) = P e^(i omaga t) e^(-i alpha
      x) e^(beta x), where the imaginary part of the complex wavenumber k = alpha + i beta accounts
      for damping. The wavenumber can be obtained as k = omega/c = omega sqrt(rho/K), where the
      equivalent density rho and equivalent bulk modulus K are complex and depend on the frequency.
      The rational function approximation of the equivalent fluid, required for the TDEF formulation
      is provided in the .mat file. </description>
  </documentation>

  <fileFormats>
    <input>
      <hdf5 fileName="TDEFwNRBC2D.h5ref" />
    </input>
    <output>
      <hdf5 id="id_h5" />
    </output>
    <materialData file="mat.xml" format="xml" />
  </fileFormats>

  <domain geometryType="plane">
    <variableList>
      <var name="freq_src" value="1000" />
    </variableList>
    <regionList>
      <region name="eqFluid" material="porousStrong" />
    </regionList>
  </domain>

  <sequenceStep index="1">
    <analysis>
      <transient>
        <numSteps> 300 </numSteps>
        <deltaT> 1e-5 </deltaT>
      </transient>
    </analysis>
    <pdeList>
      <acoustic formulation="acouPressure">
        <regionList>
          <region name="eqFluid" timeDomainEqFluid="yes" />
        </regionList>
        <bcsAndLoads>
          <pressure name="bc_left" value="sin(2*pi*freq_src*t)" />
          <absorbingBCs name="bc_right" volumeRegion="eqFluid" targetFrequency="1000" />
          <!-- Note: 
           * Currently, variables cannot be used for the targetFrequency (only numerical value allowed)
           * The target frequency of the NRBC depends on the distance from the source because of  
            the dispersive nature, causing a shift in frequency of the wave pulse of the material -->
        </bcsAndLoads>
        <storeResults>
          <nodeResult type="acouPressure">
            <allRegions saveBegin="0" saveInc="10" />
            <!-- Note: not all time steps stored to save storage -->
          </nodeResult>
        </storeResults>
      </acoustic>
    </pdeList>
  </sequenceStep>

  <sequenceStep index="2">
    <analysis>
      <harmonic>
        <numFreq>1</numFreq>
        <startFreq>freq_src</startFreq>
        <stopFreq>freq_src</stopFreq>
      </harmonic>
    </analysis>
    <pdeList>
      <acoustic formulation="acouPressure">
        <regionList>
          <region name="eqFluid" complexFluid="yes" useRationalMatApproximation="yes" />
        </regionList>
        <bcsAndLoads>
          <pressure name="bc_left" value="1" />
          <absorbingBCs name="bc_right" volumeRegion="eqFluid" />
        </bcsAndLoads>
        <storeResults>
          <nodeResult type="acouPressure">
            <allRegions />
          </nodeResult>
        </storeResults>
      </acoustic>
    </pdeList>
  </sequenceStep>

</cfsSimulation>